org.knime.core.node.config.base

Interface ConfigBaseWO

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConfigWO, ModelContentWO, NodeSettingsWO
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Config, ConfigBase, ModelContent, NodeSettings

    public interface ConfigBaseWO
    Write-only interface for ConfigBase objects providing only only write access functions for base data types..
    Author:
    Thomas Gabriel, University of Konstanz

      • addPassword

        void addPassword(String key,
                 String encryptionKey,
                 String value)
        Adds a password to the config object. The encryption routine is initialized with the given encryption key. Use the corresponding methods from ConfigBaseRO with the same encryption key in order to the get the decrypted password.
        Parameters:
        key - the key for storing the password, must not be null
        encryptionKey - key used for encrypting the password
        value - the password, may be null

      • addTransientString

        void addTransientString(String key,
                        String value)
        Adds a 'transient' string to this settings tree. A transient string is usually a password that should be kept only in main memory and never saved to disc. Consequently, when a settings object is read from disc the string will be missing (null).
        Parameters:
        key - the key for lookup
        value - that value (password)
        Since:
        5.3
        See Also:
        ConfigBaseRO.getTransientString(String)
